crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a highly obfuscated malicious binary, likely a downloader or modular trojan. It employs significant anti-analysis and stealth techniques, including extensive string and data obfuscation using a recurring XOR constant (0x22065fed). Key behaviors include dynamic API resolution by manually walking the PEB (Process Environment Block) and LDR (Loader) structures (sub_40581d, sub_40a5fb), cross-process awareness through TEB/PEB session ID and UniqueProcessID checks (sub_4082bf), and the implementation of AES-like cryptographic routines (sub_404cd8). The binary also contains logic for reconstructing payloads from XOR-encoded resources and exhibits junk code patterns at the entry point to evade simple heuristic scanners. IOCs include the recurring XOR key 0x22065fed and Base64-like custom encoding tables.
